## Proposed Changes

### Backend Database — SQLite

#### [NEW] [database.js](file:///d:/Averon/database.js)

Replace JSON files with a proper **SQLite database** using `better-sqlite3` (embedded, no separate server needed).

**Tables:**

| Table | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| `users` | User accounts, names, organizations |
| `wallets` | Blockchain wallet keys per user |
| `averon_coins` | Coin balances, purchase history |
| `assets` | Listed real-world assets |
| `asset_documents` | Uploaded documents per asset |
| `ai_analyses` | AI analysis results (valuation, risk, verdict) |
| `asset_tokens` | Tokenized chunks of an asset |
| `token_holdings` | Which user owns which tokens |
| `investments` | Investment records |
| `capital_raises` | Funded assets, payout records |
| `coin_orders` | P2P buy/sell order book |
| `coin_trades` | Completed P2P trades |
| `transactions` | All blockchain transactions |
| `blocks` | All mined blocks |
| `price_history` | Averon Coin price over time |
| `notifications` | User notifications |

**Schema highlights:**
```sql
CREATE TABLE assets (
  id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY,
  owner_id TEXT NOT NULL,
  title TEXT NOT NULL,
  description TEXT,
  category TEXT,             -- 'shares', 'land', 'commodity', 'inventory', 'equipment', etc.
  ai_verified BOOLEAN DEFAULT 0,
  ai_valuation REAL,         -- AI-determined value in INR
  ai_risk_score REAL,        -- 0.0 (safe) to 1.0 (risky)
  ai_risk_level TEXT,        -- 'LOW', 'MEDIUM', 'HIGH'
  ai_analysis_summary TEXT,  -- AI explanation
  total_value REAL,          -- Verified asset value
  raise_amount REAL,         -- How much the owner wants to raise
  token_count INTEGER,       -- How many tokens AI created
  token_price REAL,          -- Price per token in Averon Coin
  status TEXT DEFAULT 'pending_review', -- pending_review → ai_analyzing → verified → active → funded → rejected
  funded_amount REAL DEFAULT 0,
  payout_status TEXT DEFAULT 'pending', -- pending → processing → paid
  created_at INTEGER,
  deadline INTEGER
);

CREATE TABLE asset_tokens (
  id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY,
  asset_id INTEGER,
  token_index INTEGER,       -- Token #1, #2, ... #N
  owner_id TEXT,             -- Current owner (NULL = available)
  price REAL,                -- Price in Averon Coin
  purchased_at INTEGER,
  FOREIGN KEY (asset_id) REFERENCES assets(id)
);
```

